## Code Guidelines

### Always Maintain

- **Accessibility:** WCAG 2.1 AA compliance (ARIA labels, keyboard nav, screen readers)
- **RTL Support:** Works for Hebrew, Arabic, and other RTL languages
- **Dark Mode:** All components support light and dark themes
- **Multilingual:** All user-facing text uses `data-i18n` attributes
- **Mobile Responsive:** Works on 375px to 1920px+ viewports
- **Performance:** Lighthouse scores 90+ performance, 100 accessibility

### Code Patterns to Follow

- **HTML:** BEM naming convention, semantic HTML, Nunjucks templating
- **SCSS:** Component-based, use variables/mixins, CSS custom properties for theming
- **JavaScript:** Vanilla ES6+, no frameworks, class-based components for complex UI
- **Accessibility:** Proper ARIA, keyboard navigation, focus management
- **Translations:** Use `data-i18n` for all text, dot notation for nested keys

### Don'ts

- Don't use jQuery or other frameworks
- Don't hardcode colors (use CSS custom properties)
- Don't hardcode text (use `data-i18n` attributes)
- Don't skip ARIA labels or accessibility features
- Don't use directional properties without RTL overrides
- Don't break dark mode support

## File Structure

```
src/
├── _data/site.js          # Site configuration
├── _includes/
│   ├── layouts/           # Page layouts
│   ├── components/        # Reusable UI components
│   └── partials/          # Small snippets
├── assets/
│   ├── scss/             # Organized SCSS
│   ├── js/               # JavaScript modules
│   │   └── translations/ # Translation files
│   └── images/           # Images and assets
├── blog/                 # Blog posts (Markdown)
└── index.html            # Homepage
```

## Common Tasks

- **Add new language:** Copy `translations/_template.js`, translate, register in `index.js` and `site.js`
- **Add new section:** Create HTML, SCSS component, add dark/RTL styles, add translations
- **Customize colors:** Edit `_variables.scss`, update CSS custom properties
- **Add new page:** Create `.html` file with frontmatter, add translations, link from nav

See [customization-guide.md](./.ai/context/customization-guide.md) for detailed steps.

